    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-07T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-07T13:00:00-05:00" n="399"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d399">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/9088</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Special Representative</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HEM1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">House</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-07T18:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 7, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received November 7, 2.04 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>55. Your No. 15, November 7, 11 a.m. Armistice has not yet been signed. German
                    representatives will not meet Marshal <persName corresp="#p_FF1">Foch</persName>
                    until this afternoon at 5 o’clock. The terms of the armistice must not be
                    published until it is a fact that signed. We will notify you promptly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HEM1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Edward House</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
